<paragraph blockId="44.[806,1422,410,1321]" pageId="44" pageNumber="489">
<emphasis box="[806,907,410,431]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="489">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Hessler RR &amp; Martin JW" box="[921,1261,410,432]" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" pagination="645 - 661" refId="ref67925" refString="Hessler RR, Martin JW. 1989. Austinograea williamsi, new genus, new species, a hydrothermal vent crab (Decapoda: Bythograeidae) from the Mariana Back-Arc Basin, western Pacific. Journal of Crustacean Biology 9 (4): 645 - 661." type="journal article" year="1989">Hessler &amp; Martin (1989: 645)</bibRefCitation>
lamented the fact that this species was erected ‘on the basis of a single megalopa larva and on the assumption that some of the smaller juveniles described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams AB" box="[1240,1422,502,524]" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" pagination="443 - 472" refId="ref80814" refString="Williams AB. 1980. A new crab family from the vicinity of submarine thermal vents on the Galapagos Rift (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 93 (2): 443 - 472." type="journal article" year="1980">Williams (1980)</bibRefCitation>
were of this previously described species’ (see also Guinot, 1997, in 
<bibRefCitation author="Desbruyeres D &amp; Segonzac M" box="[1026,1410,563,585]" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" refId="ref64710" refString="Desbruyeres D, Segonzac M, eds. 1997. Handbook of deepsea hydrothermal vent fauna. Brest: IFREMER." type="book" year="1997">Desbruyères &amp; Segonzac, 1997</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot D &amp; Hurtado LA" box="[806,1097,594,616]" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" pagination="423 - 439" refId="ref66728" refString="Guinot D, Hurtado LA. 2003. Two new species of hydrothermal vent crabs of the genus Bythograea from the southern East Pacific Rise and from the Galapagos Rift (Crustacea Decapoda Brachyura Bythograeidae). Comptes Rendus Biologies 326: 423 - 439." type="journal article" year="2003">Guinot &amp; Hurtado (2003)</bibRefCitation>
clarified this by noting that 
<bibRefCitation author="de Saint Laurent M" box="[806,1085,625,647]" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" pagination="99 - 107" refId="ref75666" refString="de Saint Laurent M. 1988. Les megalopes et jeunes stades crabe de trois especes du genre Bythograea Williams, 1980 (Crustacea Decapoda Brachyura). Oceanologica Acta 1988: 99 - 107." type="journal article" year="1988">de Saint Laurent (1988)</bibRefCitation>
actually never saw the juvenile she selected as the 
<typeStatus box="[1113,1210,655,677]" pageId="44" pageNumber="489">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DE SAINT LAURENT" authorityYear="1988" box="[1261,1414,655,677]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bythograeidae" genus="Bythograea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis box="[1261,1414,655,677]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="489">B. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which came from a lot of juveniles identified by Williams as 
<taxonomicName box="[954,1117,717,738]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bythograeidae" genus="Bythograea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thermydron">
<emphasis box="[954,1117,717,738]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="489">B. thermydron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. About this lot, 
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot D &amp; Hurtado LA" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" pagination="423 - 439" refId="ref66728" refString="Guinot D, Hurtado LA. 2003. Two new species of hydrothermal vent crabs of the genus Bythograea from the southern East Pacific Rise and from the Galapagos Rift (Crustacea Decapoda Brachyura Bythograeidae). Comptes Rendus Biologies 326: 423 - 439." type="journal article" year="2003">Guinot &amp; Hurtado (2003: 432)</bibRefCitation>
stated: ‘The exact locality of the juvenile material of Williams, which perhaps contains 
<taxonomicName box="[806,968,809,830]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bythograeidae" genus="Bythograea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thermydron">
<emphasis box="[806,968,809,830]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="489">B. thermydron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mixed with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DE SAINT LAURENT" authorityYear="1988" box="[1111,1265,809,830]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bythograeidae" genus="Bythograea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis box="[1111,1265,809,830]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="489">B. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is unknown.’ Furthermore, the 
<typeStatus box="[1013,1110,839,861]" pageId="44" pageNumber="489">holotype</typeStatus>
is actually a juvenile (now 
<collectionCode box="[806,885,870,891]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" type="Museum">USNM</collectionCode>
268862), and the megalopa noted above is a 
<typeStatus box="[806,908,901,922]" pageId="44" pageNumber="489">paratype</typeStatus>
(now 
<collectionCode box="[977,1056,901,922]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" type="Museum">USNM</collectionCode>
180065), according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot D &amp; Hurtado LA" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" pagination="423 - 439" refId="ref66728" refString="Guinot D, Hurtado LA. 2003. Two new species of hydrothermal vent crabs of the genus Bythograea from the southern East Pacific Rise and from the Galapagos Rift (Crustacea Decapoda Brachyura Bythograeidae). Comptes Rendus Biologies 326: 423 - 439." type="journal article" year="2003">Guinot &amp; Hurtado (2003)</bibRefCitation>
. The similarity between de Saint Laurent’s description and specimen and the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="GUINOT &amp; HURTADO" authorityYear="2003" box="[806,983,993,1014]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bythograeidae" genus="Bythograea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="galapagensis">
<emphasis box="[806,983,993,1014]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="489">B. galapagensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Guinot &amp; Hurtado is such that comparisons ‘do not allow us to establish whether they correspond to the same species’ (
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot D &amp; Hurtado LA" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" pagination="423 - 439" refId="ref66728" refString="Guinot D, Hurtado LA. 2003. Two new species of hydrothermal vent crabs of the genus Bythograea from the southern East Pacific Rise and from the Galapagos Rift (Crustacea Decapoda Brachyura Bythograeidae). Comptes Rendus Biologies 326: 423 - 439." type="journal article" year="2003">Guinot &amp; Hurtado, 2003: 432</bibRefCitation>
). Because the species description ‘was based on a total of six early crab stages and a megalopa, all mixed with 
<taxonomicName box="[948,1111,1146,1168]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bythograeidae" genus="Bythograea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thermydron">
<emphasis box="[948,1111,1146,1168]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="489">B. thermydron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens from the original collection of the 
<collectingRegion box="[1049,1168,1177,1199]" country="Ecuador" name="Galapagos" pageId="44" pageNumber="489">Galapagos</collectingRegion>
Rift studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams AB" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" pagination="443 - 472" refId="ref80814" refString="Williams AB. 1980. A new crab family from the vicinity of submarine thermal vents on the Galapagos Rift (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 93 (2): 443 - 472." type="journal article" year="1980">Williams (1980)</bibRefCitation>
,’ 
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot D &amp; Hurtado LA" box="[957,1246,1207,1230]" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" pagination="423 - 439" refId="ref66728" refString="Guinot D, Hurtado LA. 2003. Two new species of hydrothermal vent crabs of the genus Bythograea from the southern East Pacific Rise and from the Galapagos Rift (Crustacea Decapoda Brachyura Bythograeidae). Comptes Rendus Biologies 326: 423 - 439." type="journal article" year="2003">Guinot &amp; Hurtado (2003)</bibRefCitation>
felt that this is ‘a poorly known species’. We agree with that assessment and believe that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DE SAINT LAURENT" authorityYear="1988" box="[1063,1216,1269,1290]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bythograeidae" genus="Bythograea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="44" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis box="[1063,1216,1269,1290]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="489">B. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is of questionable status and in need of re-evaluation.
</paragraph>
